{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":452,"text":"Do you think the world is going\nto be a better place next year?"},{"time":6120,"text":"In the next decade?"},{"time":8657,"text":"Can we end hunger,"},{"time":11444,"text":"achieve gender equality,"},{"time":13999,"text":"halt climate change,"},{"time":16145,"text":"all in the next 15 years?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":19764,"text":"Well, according to the governments\nof the world, yes we can."},{"time":24343,"text":"In the last few days,\nthe leaders of the world,"},{"time":26985,"text":"meeting at the UN in New York,"},{"time":29485,"text":"agreed a new set of Global Goals"},{"time":32264,"text":"for the development of the world to 2030."},{"time":35493,"text":"And here they are:"},{"time":36940,"text":"these goals are the product\nof a massive consultation exercise."},{"time":41658,"text":"The Global Goals are who we,\nhumanity, want to be."}]},{"cues":[{"time":47423,"text":"Now that's the plan, but can we get there?"},{"time":51599,"text":"Can this vision for a better world\nreally be achieved?"},{"time":56247,"text":"Well, I'm here today because\nwe've run the numbers,"},{"time":60031,"text":"and the answer, shockingly,"},{"time":64599,"text":"is that maybe we actually can."},{"time":67599,"text":"But not with business as usual."}]},{"cues":[{"time":71757,"text":"Now, the idea that the world\nis going to get a better place"},{"time":74836,"text":"may seem a little fanciful."},{"time":77170,"text":"Watch the news every day and the world\nseems to be going backwards, not forwards."},{"time":81599,"text":"And let's be frank:"},{"time":83321,"text":"it's pretty easy to be skeptical\nabout grand announcements"},{"time":86599,"text":"coming out of the UN."}]},{"cues":[{"time":89067,"text":"But please, I invite you to suspend\nyour disbelief for just a moment."},{"time":93956,"text":"Because back in 2001,"},{"time":95877,"text":"the UN agreed another set of goals,\nthe Millennium Development Goals."},{"time":101138,"text":"And the flagship target there\nwas to halve the proportion of people"},{"time":105362,"text":"living in poverty by 2015."},{"time":109072,"text":"The target was to take\nfrom a baseline of 1990,"},{"time":112913,"text":"when 36 percent of the world's\npopulation lived in poverty,"},{"time":116599,"text":"to get to 18 percent poverty this year."}]},{"cues":[{"time":120599,"text":"Did we hit this target?"},{"time":122599,"text":"Well, no, we didn't."},{"time":124599,"text":"We exceeded it."},{"time":126677,"text":"This year, global poverty\nis going to fall to 12 percent."},{"time":131804,"text":"Now, that's still not good enough,"},{"time":133599,"text":"and the world does still have\nplenty of problems."},{"time":137242,"text":"But the pessimists and doomsayers\nwho say that the world can't get better"},{"time":142701,"text":"are simply wrong."}]},{"cues":[{"time":145748,"text":"So how did we achieve this success?"},{"time":148002,"text":"Well, a lot of it was because\nof economic growth."},{"time":151383,"text":"Some of the biggest reductions in poverty\nwere in countries such as China and India,"},{"time":156599,"text":"which have seen rapid\neconomic growth in recent years."},{"time":160898,"text":"So can we pull off the same trick again?"},{"time":163934,"text":"Can economic growth\nget us to the Global Goals?"},{"time":168642,"text":"Well, to answer that question,"},{"time":170405,"text":"we need to benchmark where the world\nis today against the Global Goals"},{"time":174599,"text":"and figure out how far we have to travel."}]},{"cues":[{"time":178046,"text":"But that ain't easy,"},{"time":179973,"text":"because the Global Goals\naren't just ambitious,"},{"time":182814,"text":"they're also pretty complicated."},{"time":185599,"text":"Over 17 goals, there are then 169 targets"},{"time":189767,"text":"and literally hundreds of indicators."},{"time":193444,"text":"Also, while some of the goals\nare pretty specific --"},{"time":197072,"text":"end hunger --"},{"time":198519,"text":"others are a lot vaguer --"},{"time":200439,"text":"promote peaceful and tolerant societies."}]},{"cues":[{"time":203924,"text":"So to help us with this benchmarking,"},{"time":205873,"text":"I'm going to use a tool\ncalled the Social Progress Index."},{"time":210166,"text":"What this does is measures all the stuff\nthe Global Goals are trying to achieve,"},{"time":214144,"text":"but sums it up into a single number\nthat we can use as our benchmark"},{"time":218330,"text":"and track progress over time."}]},{"cues":[{"time":220900,"text":"The Social Progress Index basically asks\nthree fundamental questions"},{"time":224477,"text":"about a society."},{"time":226214,"text":"First of all, does everyone have\nthe basic needs of survival:"},{"time":229703,"text":"food, water, shelter, safety?"},{"time":232535,"text":"Secondly, does everyone have\nthe building blocks of a better life:"},{"time":236313,"text":"education, information, health\nand a sustainable environment?"},{"time":241153,"text":"And does everyone have\nthe opportunity to improve their lives,"},{"time":244863,"text":"through rights, freedom of choice,\nfreedom from discrimination,"},{"time":248887,"text":"and access to the world's\nmost advanced knowledge?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":252463,"text":"The Social Progress Index sums all this\ntogether using 52 indicators"},{"time":256599,"text":"to create an aggregate score\non a scale of 0 to 100."},{"time":261436,"text":"And what we find is that there's\na wide diversity of performance"},{"time":264623,"text":"in the world today."},{"time":266189,"text":"The highest performing country,\nNorway, scores 88."},{"time":270281,"text":"The lowest performing country,\nCentral African Republic, scores 31."},{"time":275599,"text":"And we can add up\nall the countries together,"},{"time":277719,"text":"weighting for the different\npopulation sizes,"},{"time":280177,"text":"and that global score is 61."},{"time":284160,"text":"In concrete terms,"},{"time":285335,"text":"that means that the average human being\nis living on a level of social progress"},{"time":289117,"text":"about the same of Cuba\nor Kazakhstan today."}]},{"cues":[{"time":293229,"text":"That's where we are today: 61 out of 100."},{"time":296420,"text":"What do we have to get to\nto achieve the Global Goals?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":300254,"text":"Now, the Global Goals\nare certainly ambitious,"},{"time":302766,"text":"but they're not about turning the world\ninto Norway in just 15 years."},{"time":307395,"text":"So having looked at the numbers,\nmy estimate is that a score of 75"},{"time":311518,"text":"would not only be a giant leap forward\nin human well-being,"},{"time":315599,"text":"it would also count as hitting\nthe Global Goals target."},{"time":319412,"text":"So there's our target, 75 out of 100."},{"time":322222,"text":"Can we get there?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":324275,"text":"Well, the Social Progress Index\ncan help us calculate this,"},{"time":327283,"text":"because as you might have noticed,"},{"time":328973,"text":"there are no economic indicators in there;"},{"time":331222,"text":"there's no GDP or economic growth\nin the Social Progress Index model."},{"time":336032,"text":"And what that lets us do\nis understand the relationship"},{"time":339599,"text":"between economic growth\nand social progress."}]},{"cues":[{"time":343749,"text":"Let me show you on this chart."},{"time":345393,"text":"So here on the vertical axis,\nI've put social progress,"},{"time":348599,"text":"the stuff the Global Goals\nare trying to achieve."},{"time":351191,"text":"Higher is better."},{"time":352761,"text":"And then on the horizontal axis,\nis GDP per capita."},{"time":356169,"text":"Further to the right means richer."},{"time":358732,"text":"And in there, I'm now going to put\nall the countries of the world,"},{"time":362056,"text":"each one represented by a dot,"},{"time":364188,"text":"and on top of that I'm going to put\nthe regression line"},{"time":366807,"text":"that shows the average relationship."},{"time":369161,"text":"And what this tells us\nis that as we get richer,"},{"time":372715,"text":"social progress does tend to improve."},{"time":376072,"text":"However, as we get richer,\neach extra dollar of GDP"},{"time":380687,"text":"is buying us less and less\nsocial progress."},{"time":385109,"text":"And now we can use this information\nto start building our forecast."},{"time":389403,"text":"So here is the world in 2015."},{"time":392718,"text":"We have a social progress score of 61"},{"time":396140,"text":"and a GDP per capita of $14,000."},{"time":399895,"text":"And the place we're trying to get to,\nremember, is 75, that Global Goals target."},{"time":404147,"text":"So here we are today,\n$14,000 per capita GDP."},{"time":408290,"text":"How rich are we going to be in 2030?"},{"time":410679,"text":"That's what we need to know next."},{"time":412541,"text":"Well, the best forecast we can find comes\nfrom the US Department of Agriculture,"},{"time":416816,"text":"which forecasts 3.1 percent\naverage global economic growth"},{"time":421491,"text":"over the next 15 years,"},{"time":423259,"text":"which means that in 2030,\nif they're right,"},{"time":426402,"text":"per capita GDP will be about $23,000."},{"time":431293,"text":"So now the question is:\nif we get that much richer,"},{"time":433858,"text":"how much social progress\nare we going to get?"},{"time":436747,"text":"Well, we asked a team\nof economists at Deloitte"},{"time":439381,"text":"who checked and crunched the numbers,"},{"time":441174,"text":"and they came back and said, well, look:\nif the world's average wealth goes"},{"time":446150,"text":"from $14,000 a year to $23,000 a year,"},{"time":449950,"text":"social progress is going to increase"},{"time":452262,"text":"from 61 to 62.4."}]},{"cues":[{"time":456926,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":458863,"text":"Just 62.4. Just a tiny increase."}]},{"cues":[{"time":464315,"text":"Now this seems a bit strange."},{"time":465886,"text":"Economic growth seems\nto have really helped"},{"time":468122,"text":"in the fight against poverty,"},{"time":469835,"text":"but it doesn't seem\nto be having much impact"},{"time":472059,"text":"on trying to get to the Global Goals."},{"time":474467,"text":"So what's going on?"},{"time":476182,"text":"Well, I think there are two things."},{"time":477897,"text":"The first is that in a way,\nwe're the victims of our own success."},{"time":481788,"text":"We've used up the easy wins\nfrom economic growth,"},{"time":484804,"text":"and now we're moving on\nto harder problems."},{"time":487650,"text":"And also, we know that economic growth\ncomes with costs as well as benefits."},{"time":492062,"text":"There are costs to the environment, costs\nfrom new health problems like obesity."}]},{"cues":[{"time":497825,"text":"So that's the bad news."},{"time":499531,"text":"We're not going to get to the Global Goals\njust by getting richer."}]},{"cues":[{"time":504211,"text":"So are the pessimists right?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":506599,"text":"Well, maybe not."},{"time":507965,"text":"Because the Social Progress Index\nalso has some very good news."},{"time":512683,"text":"Let me take you back\nto that regression line."},{"time":515066,"text":"So this is the average relationship\nbetween GDP and social progress,"},{"time":518470,"text":"and this is what our\nlast forecast was based on."},{"time":522040,"text":"But as you saw already,"},{"time":523737,"text":"there is actually lots of noise\naround this trend line."}]},{"cues":[{"time":528471,"text":"What that tells us, quite simply,"},{"time":530932,"text":"is that GDP is not destiny."},{"time":534589,"text":"We have countries that are underperforming"},{"time":537091,"text":"on social progress,\nrelative to their wealth."},{"time":540321,"text":"Russia has lots\nof natural resource wealth,"},{"time":542695,"text":"but lots of social problems."},{"time":544871,"text":"China has boomed economically,"},{"time":547126,"text":"but hasn't made much headway\non human rights or environmental issues."},{"time":551930,"text":"India has a space program\nand millions of people without toilets."},{"time":557264,"text":"Now, on the other hand, we have countries\nthat are overperforming"},{"time":560585,"text":"on social progress relative to their GDP."},{"time":563922,"text":"Costa Rica has prioritized education,\nhealth and environmental sustainability,"},{"time":569657,"text":"and as a result, it's achieving\na very high level of social progress,"},{"time":573602,"text":"despite only having a rather modest GDP."},{"time":577471,"text":"And Costa Rica's not alone."},{"time":579599,"text":"From poor countries like Rwanda\nto richer countries like New Zealand,"},{"time":583599,"text":"we see that it's possible to get\nlots of social progress,"},{"time":587221,"text":"even if your GDP is not so great."}]},{"cues":[{"time":590649,"text":"And that's really important,\nbecause it tells us two things."},{"time":594284,"text":"First of all, it tells us that we already\nin the world have the solutions"},{"time":599516,"text":"to many of the problems\nthat the Global Goals are trying to solve."},{"time":603879,"text":"It also tells us\nthat we're not slaves to GDP."},{"time":608029,"text":"Our choices matter: if we prioritize\nthe well-being of people,"},{"time":612328,"text":"then we can make a lot more progress\nthan our GDP might expect."}]},{"cues":[{"time":617008,"text":"How much? Enough to get us\nto the Global Goals?"},{"time":620184,"text":"Well, let's look at some numbers."},{"time":621819,"text":"What we know already: the world today\nis scoring 61 on social progress,"},{"time":625704,"text":"and the place we want to get to is 75."},{"time":628526,"text":"If we rely on economic growth alone,"},{"time":630770,"text":"we're going to get to 62.4."},{"time":633375,"text":"So let's assume now that we can get\nthe countries that are currently"},{"time":637501,"text":"underperforming on social progress --\nthe Russia, China, Indias --"},{"time":640719,"text":"just up to the average."},{"time":642408,"text":"How much social progress does that get us?"},{"time":644623,"text":"Well, that takes us to 65."},{"time":647297,"text":"It's a bit better, but still\nquite a long way to go."},{"time":650227,"text":"So let's get a little bit more\noptimistic and say,"},{"time":652612,"text":"what if every country\ngets a little bit better"},{"time":655426,"text":"at turning its wealth into well-being?"},{"time":658194,"text":"Well then, we get to 67."},{"time":661440,"text":"And now let's be even bolder still."},{"time":664119,"text":"What if every country in the world\nchose to be like Costa Rica"},{"time":668599,"text":"in prioritizing human well-being,"},{"time":670993,"text":"using its wealth for the well-being\nof its citizens?"},{"time":673599,"text":"Well then, we get to nearly 73,\nvery close to the Global Goals."}]},{"cues":[{"time":678599,"text":"Can we achieve the Global Goals?"},{"time":680599,"text":"Certainly not with business as usual."},{"time":683278,"text":"Even a flood tide of economic growth\nis not going to get us there,"},{"time":687653,"text":"if it just raises the mega-yachts\nand the super-wealthy"},{"time":690740,"text":"and leaves the rest behind."},{"time":693177,"text":"If we're going to achieve the Global Goals\nwe have to do things differently."},{"time":697195,"text":"We have to prioritize social progress,\nand really scale solutions"},{"time":701428,"text":"around the world."},{"time":702942,"text":"I believe the Global Goals\nare a historic opportunity,"},{"time":706681,"text":"because the world's leaders\nhave promised to deliver them."},{"time":711101,"text":"Let's not dismiss the goals\nor slide into pessimism;"},{"time":715098,"text":"let's hold them to that promise."},{"time":717829,"text":"And we need to hold them to that promise\nby holding them accountable,"},{"time":721183,"text":"tracking their progress all the way\nthrough the next 15 years."}]},{"cues":[{"time":724928,"text":"And I want to finish by showing you"},{"time":726634,"text":"a way to do that, called\nthe People's Report Card."},{"time":729423,"text":"The People's Report Card brings together\nall this data into a simple framework"},{"time":734354,"text":"that we'll all be familiar\nwith from our school days,"},{"time":736918,"text":"to hold them to account."},{"time":738370,"text":"It grades our performance\non the Global Goals"},{"time":740649,"text":"on a scale from F to A,"},{"time":744144,"text":"where F is humanity at its worst,\nand A is humanity at its best."},{"time":749690,"text":"Our world today is scoring a C-."},{"time":755405,"text":"The Global Goals are all about\ngetting to an A,"},{"time":758858,"text":"and that's why we're going to be updating\nthe People's Report Card annually,"},{"time":762599,"text":"for the world and for all\nthe countries of the world,"},{"time":765836,"text":"so we can hold our leaders to account"},{"time":768451,"text":"to achieve this target\nand fulfill this promise."},{"time":773180,"text":"Because getting to the Global Goals will\nonly happen if we do things differently,"},{"time":777851,"text":"if our leaders do things differently,"},{"time":780042,"text":"and for that to happen,\nthat needs us to demand it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":784494,"text":"So let's reject business as usual."},{"time":788455,"text":"Let's demand a different path."},{"time":791365,"text":"Let's choose the world that we want."}]},{"cues":[{"time":796157,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":797333,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":802599,"text":"Bruno Giussani: Thank you, Michael."},{"time":806675,"text":"Michael, just one question:\nthe Millennium Development Goals"},{"time":809522,"text":"established 15 years ago,"},{"time":811027,"text":"they were kind of applying\nto every country"},{"time":814128,"text":"but it turned out to be really\na scorecard for emerging countries."},{"time":817719,"text":"Now the new Global Goals\nare explicitly universal."},{"time":820195,"text":"They ask for every country to show action\nand to show progress."},{"time":824371,"text":"How can I, as a private citizen,\nuse the report card"},{"time":827383,"text":"to create pressure for action?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":830241,"text":"Michael Green: This is a really important\npoint; it's a big shift in priorities --"},{"time":834140,"text":"it's no longer about poor\ncountries and just poverty."},{"time":836643,"text":"It's about every country."},{"time":837882,"text":"And every country is going to have\nchallenges in getting to the Global Goals."},{"time":841536,"text":"Even, I'm sorry to say, Bruno,\nSwitzerland has got to work to do."},{"time":844870,"text":"And so that's why we're going to produce\nthese report cards in 2016"},{"time":848264,"text":"for every country in the world."},{"time":849774,"text":"Then we can really see, how are we doing?"},{"time":851877,"text":"And it's not going to be rich countries\nscoring straight A's."},{"time":854782,"text":"And that, then, I think,\nis to provide a point of focus"},{"time":857414,"text":"for people to start demanding action\nand start demanding progress."}]},{"cues":[{"time":860894,"text":"BG: Thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":862366,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}